# Premises:
# Beijing is the capital of the People's Republic of China.
NationalCapital(beijing, peopleRepublicChina)

# Beijing is the world's most populous national capital city.
# This implies Beijing is a national capital and it is populous.
# The phrasing "world's most populous national capital city" implies a superlative,
# but for first-order logic, we can represent it as Beijing being populous
# and also being a national capital. The "most" aspect is harder to capture directly
# without more complex machinery or reification. We'll represent it as Beijing
# is populous and is a national capital.
Populous(beijing)

# Beijing is located in Northern China.
Location(beijing, northernChina)
Region(northernChina) # Assuming northernChina is a region

# Beijing hosted the 2008 Summer Olympics and 2008 Summer Paralympics Games.
Host(beijing, games2008SummerOlympics)
Event(games2008SummerOlympics)
Olympics(games2008SummerOlympics)
Summer(games2008SummerOlympics)
